President Biden has declared a state of emergency in the U.S. Virgin Islands due to elevated levels of lead and copper in the water supply. This declaration authorizes the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to save lives, protect property, and ensure public health and safety. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. The agency will provide emergency protective measures, including direct federal assistance, for water, filters, testing, and technical assistance for 90 days. Ms. Lai Sun Yee of FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.